  "text": "A. Image Benchmarks 1) Image databases: In Table I , we list many of the image datasets that are popular with the SR community. Some of the datasets have already been partitioned, by their proponents, to training/validation and testing sets; there is, however, no hard or soft rule and many works use them without restricting to these partitions. Sometimes the researchers improvise on the datasets, e.g. in [CITATION_1] , the 91 Timofte dataset is decomposed into 24,800 sub-images for training along with 395,909 images (over 5 million sub-images) from ImageNet. Similarly some authors combine more than one datasets, e.g. training 291 (91 Timofte +200BSD) from [CITATION_2] is a popular choice for training [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] .",
